The article is a transcript of remarks made by Vice President Mike Pence during his trip to Italy. He discusses the strong relationship between the United States and Italy, the importance of NATO investment, and the desire for fair and reciprocal trade with the European Union. Pence also talks about his meeting with Pope Francis, where they discussed the sanctity of life and the situation in Venezuela. He addresses questions about the President's comments regarding the Ambassador to Ukraine and the impeachment trial, stating that the President had concerns about the Ambassador and that there was no quid pro quo. Pence also expresses confidence in Rudy Giuliani and emphasizes the need to focus on issues that matter to the American people.